  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-02 07:11 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Smart Entry: Price Filter & Evening Loss Autopsy\n\n**Task:** P2 smart entry \u2014 dissect Apr 1 evening failures, analyze entry price filter, find parameter improvements\n\n**Finding \u2014 Morning vs Evening: OBI is THE Differentiator:**\n- Morning wins (n=7): avg OBI=-0.370 (bearish orderbook)\n- Evening losses (n=3): avg OBI=+0.476 (bullish orderbook)\n- Delta: 0.846 OBI spread. This is not random \u2014 bullish OB kills our contrarian strategy.\n- BTC was flat during evening (-0.03%) so it wasn't a trending market. The OBI was the signal.\n\n**Finding \u2014 Entry Price Tiers (V3+ hours, n=71):**\n| Price Range | Trades | WR | EV/trade | $/trade ($12) |\n|-------------|--------|-----|----------|---------------|\n| <$0.50 | 20 | 60% | +0.224 | +$2.69 |\n| $0.50-0.52 | 31 | 71% | +0.392 | +$4.71 |\n| $0.52-0.535 | 7 | 86% | +0.632 | +$7.58 |\n| >$0.535 | 13 | 85% | +0.574 | +$6.89 |\n\nHigher entry price = dramatically better EV (+75% more per trade at $0.50-0.52 vs <$0.50). The current min_price=$0.48 allows the weakest tier.\n\n**Finding \u2014 Edge Monotonically Predicts WR:**\n- Edge 0.15-0.20: 46% WR (LOSER)\n- Edge 0.22-0.24: 59% WR\n- Edge 0.25 (max): 68% WR\n- Edge is capped at 0.25, so max-edge trades have both high bias + favorable price. A min_edge filter could work but overlaps with min_bias (V5a).\n\n**Finding \u2014 Conviction 4/4 = 40% WR (Worse Than 3/4!):**\n- All 10 conv-4 trades were from Mar 20 (pre-V3), in bad hours (15h, 18h, 22h).\n- In V3+ hours, 4/4 conviction has NEVER occurred.\n- Not actionable \u2014 zombie-era contamination. Ignore this metric.\n\n**My thinking:** Raising min_price from $0.48 \u2192 $0.50 is low-risk, data-backed. Eliminates 28% of trades (the weakest 60% WR tier) and raises average EV by ~50%. This is simpler than V5a and could be deployed IMMEDIATELY. However, the $0.48 min was set based on earlier analysis and Apr 1 only had 2 trades in that range (1W/1L). I want 1 more week of shadow data before changing.\n\n**Decision:**\n1. Queue min_price=$0.50 for V5a deploy (Apr 6) \u2014 bundle with min_bias=45\n2. Add max_price=$0.55 widening to V6 spec for validation\n3. OBI gate (block when OBI>0.5) confirmed by evening autopsy \u2014 add to V5b spec\n4. No immediate parameter changes \u2014 let V4.1 run clean for W14 validation\n\n**Next:** P3 \u2014 V6 cooldown spec finalization\n\n---\n## 2026-04-02 06:42 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Copy Intel: HL Order Book + OBI Performance Deep Dive\n\n**Task:** P1 copy intelligence \u2014 analyze HL whale order book positioning post-selloff, validate OBI signal on cumulative data\n\n**Finding \u2014 HL Order Book is Balanced (Not Bearish):**\n- Initial snapshot showed massive -0.876 OBI. At higher resolution ($1 levels): Bids=69.6 BTC vs Asks=49.2 BTC \u2192 actually BID-heavy.\n- Major support wall: 16.35 BTC ($1.09M) at $66,508. Support at $66,512-$66,513 (11.8 BTC).\n- Sell pressure distributed evenly across $66,523-$66,542 \u2014 no single mega wall, just steady sell",
